A N A C T
RELATING TO WATERS AND NAVIGATION -- WATER POLLUTION
Introduced By: Representatives Cortvriend, McGaw, Speakman, Fogarty, Kislak,
Carson, and Morales
Date Introduced: February 28, 2025
Referred To: House Environment and Natural Resources
It is enacted by the General Assembly as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 46-12 of the General Laws entitled "Water Pollution" is hereby
2 amended by adding thereto the following section:
3 46-12-42. Testing of biosolids.
4 (a) Any applicant seeking an order of approval from the department of environmental
5 management for the distribution or land application of biosolids shall test its biosolids for PFAS
6 contaminants, as that term is defined by ยง 46-32-2, and the results shall be submitted to the
7 department with the application for the order of approval.
8 (b) Any operators with an existing order of approval for the distribution or land application
9 of biosolids shall test its biosolids quarterly for PFAS contaminants, as that term is defined by ยง
10 46-32-2, and submit the results to the department by the last day of each calendar quarter. Sampling
11 shall commence during the October 2025 to December 2025 quarter, with the first round of results
12 submitted to the department no later than December 31, 2025.
13 (c) The director is authorized to reject any application for an order of approval on the basis
14 that approval of said application would pose an environmental threat or pose a risk to public health,
15 safety, or welfare.
16 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect on September 1, 2025.
