EXPLANATION
BY THE LEGISLATIVE COUNCIL
OF
A N A C T
RELATING TO WATERS AND NAVIGATION -- WATER POLLUTION
***
1 This act would, effective September 1, 2025, require persons seeking to apply biosolids to
2 lands to test the biosolids for PFAS contaminants on a quarterly basis and report those findings to
3 the department of environmental management. This act would authorize the director to reject
4 applications seeking distribution of biosolids to lands for environmental threat or risk to public
5 health, safety, or welfare.
6 This act would take effect on September 1, 2025.
